<refsection condition='ref.description'>
<title>Description</title>


<para>A <tag>QandASet</tag> is a list consisting of
<tag>Question</tag>s and <tag>Answer</tag>s.
<tag>QandASet</tag>s can be divided into sections.
</para>

<para>Every entry in a <tag>QandASet</tag> must contain a
<tag>Question</tag>, but <tag>Answer</tag>s are
optional (some questions have no answers), and may be repeated (some
questions have more than one answer).
</para>

<para>Common uses for <tag>QandASet</tag>s include reader
questionnaires and lists of <quote>Frequently Asked Questions</quote>
(<acronym>FAQ</acronym>s). For the purpose of an
<acronym>FAQ</acronym>, DocBook <acronym>V3.1</acronym> added the
<literal>FAQ</literal> class to <tag>Article</tag>.
</para>

<refsection><title>Processing expectations</title>
<para><?tdg gentext='format.block'?>
The <tag class='attribute'>DefaultLabel</tag>
attribute has a significant influence on the presentation of
<tag>Question</tag>s and <tag>Answer</tag>s.
</para>
</refsection>


